FT  18 JUL 94 / Business Travel (Update): Russia to Japan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Aeroflot, the Russian international airline, opened a new route from the far
eastern city of Vladivostok to the central Japanese town of Toyama last
Friday.
Aeroflot will fly the route once a week, using Tupolev Tu-154 airliners,
which can carry about 160 passengers.
