<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Lower tax credit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Since when have public limited companies been giving a tax credit of 20 per
cent on dividends instead of 25? Also, for how many years is a taxpayer
supposed to keep dividend tax vouchers and other tax records?
Norman Lamont, then chancellor of the exchequer, cut advance corporation tax
to 20 per cent in his March 1993 Budget. Generally, it would be wise to
retain tax papers for seven years if there are likely to be any queries or
reclaims involved. (Murray Johnstone).
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All enquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
